    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Chop your<strong> potatoes </strong>(skins on) into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-tray-tartiflette-inspired-sausage-and-potato-bake/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes </strong>to a large, <strong>oven-proof dish</strong> (or two!) with the <strong>sliced onion</strong> and your <strong>sausages</strong></p><p>Add a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-tray-tartiflette-inspired-sausage-and-potato-bake/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Put the dish[es] in the oven and cook for an initial 15-20 min, then give eveything a good mix up</p><p>Return the dish[es] to the oven and cook for a final 15-20 min or until the potatoes are golden and tender and the sausages are cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-tray-tartiflette-inspired-sausage-and-potato-bake/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong> finely</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-tray-tartiflette-inspired-sausage-and-potato-bake/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add 100ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [130ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [170ml]</span> <strong>milk</strong> to a heatproof jug with the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, your <strong>Chinese rice wine, grated cheddar</strong>, your <strong>cornflour </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>pepper </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>tartiflette-inspired sauce</strong></p><p>When the dish[es] are almost cooked, add the <strong>tartiflette-inspired sauce </strong>to the<strong> microwave</strong> for 2-3 min or until thickened and steaming hot, then stir it all together</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-tray-tartiflette-inspired-sausage-and-potato-bake/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once cooked, remove the dish[es] from the oven and pour the <strong>tartiflette-inspired sauce </strong>all over, tilting the dish a little so the sauce gets to all the edges of the dish[es]</p><p>Return the dish[es] to the oven for a final 5-8 min or until everything is bubbling and golden \u2013 this is your <strong>one tray</strong> <strong>tartiflette-inspired sausage and potato bake</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-tray-tartiflette-inspired-sausage-and-potato-bake/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your<strong> salad</strong> and pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Add your<strong> cider vinegar</strong> to a large bowl with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, <strong>pepper </strong>and<strong> sugar </strong>and whisk together \u2013 this is your <strong>dressing</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>salad</strong> to the dressing and toss \u2013 this is your <strong>dressed salad</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-tray-tartiflette-inspired-sausage-and-potato-bake/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>one tray tartiflette-inspired sausage and potato bake</strong> with the <strong>dressed salad</strong> to the side</p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
